      <div class="annotationBody">
        
        <div><p>I think this is why we need to really focus on the idea of being "tool agnostic", a phrase I'm digging into in my current writing and something I thought about while teaching in a Title I. school. Technology tools will change. Our responsibility is to ensure our students master skills. </p>

<p>This is why I get frustrated when I see things like PD's offered on Pear Deck, instead of a PD focusing on what Pear Deck (or quizlet, or pinterest, or google forms, etc. etc. etc.) is asking students to do? Trends change, free apps disappear or go behind paywalls, change happens. </p></div>
