        <div><p>I can certainly agree with and understand this point, especially given the recent demise of sites like Kidblog and Wikispaces. In the same way, we also need to help teachers find "a domain of one's own," outside of the school LMS, and as a way to create their own professional digital identity. That way, they can learn how HTML (and GIFs, and embed codes, and other types of media) function, and can make those tools – and their purposes – explicit in digital writing instruction.</p></div>
