      <div class="annotationBody">
        
        <div><p>I am torn on this one -- of schoolifying the spaces where kids hang out. On one hand, as a teacher, it opens the door to authentic learning. On the other, it sucks the fun and purity of why they are there in the first place, to carve out identity. I sometimes feel like the interloper, and sense them running to find another digital crawl space to have the kinds of interaction they really want to have.</p></div>
